The course gives an overview of the basic Latin grammar, translation exercises are done, and Latin authors are selectively read. Influences of Latin to modern languages are brought out.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of thee course is to give an overview of the Latin language, which is a crucial skill for every linguist and humanitarian. The course also helps students to notice the connections between Latin and Romance languages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The course gives an overview of the basic grammar of Latin. By the end of the course, students are able to determine the forms of nouns and ajectives, of verbs in different tenses, using some assisting materials. They are able to translate different participle forms, to identify the most common pronouns and tranlate simpler texts in Latin. Students are aware of constructions "accusativus cum infinitivo" , "nominativus cum infinitivo" and "ablativus absolutus", are able to generally analyze the sentences and construct simpler texts in Latin by themselves. The student knows how to use dictionaries and most important internet resources for finding and translating Latin texts.
